<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA78">
<l>araṇā namakkeṉṟu māḻi valavaṉ</l>
<l>muraṉāḷ valañcuḻinta moympaṉ – caraṇāmē</l>
<l>lētukati yētunilai yētupiṟap peṉṉātē</l>
<l>yōtukati māyaṉaiyē yōrttu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Refuge for us is always the one with the discus on his right<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Or: “the one who masters the discus”.</note>. If there is refuge</l>
<l>[it is] the one by whose prowess the strength [and] the days of Muraṉ<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Viṣṇu is known as Murāri because he destroyed the Asura Mura whose arrogance had begun to threaten the world.</note> were curbed.</l>
<l>Without asking ‘which way, which condition, which birth?’</l>
<l>recite, perceiving the Dark one as the way.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
